description:
SyncPort: Table recording synchronization port configuration information for each cell, including timestamps, location, identifiers, data type, format version, user label, port ID, and reservation details.
dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
Area_Name: Name of the area where the cell is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3:  An identifier; likely redundant or unused.
Id4: An identifier; likely redundant or unused.
vsDataType: Type of synchronization port data.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
SyncPort.userLabel: User-defined label for the synchronization port (currently empty).
SyncPort.syncPortId: Unique identifier for the synchronization port.
SyncPort.reservedBy: Details specifying the entity reserving the synchronization port.
